# new_features.txt
ideas: Load the list file if one already exists.
       Allow multiple users to create their own to-do lists.
       Add due dates, optional due dates, times, etc.

Feature #1:
Saving list to a file. If the file already exists, the user is prompted if
they want to overwrite it.

Feature #2:
def search_by_description(description)
Search by description. The description must match exactly the description on the list.
The function prints the item's index within the list, description, and completion status.

Feature #3:
Delete all completed items.

Feature #4:
Change an item's description. This can be found in TodoList::change_description which
calls Item::change_item_description to get the user input that change the item's
instance variable @description.